00:33:08.880 --> 00:33:10.550
So, the thing that people don't usually

00:33:10.560 --> 00:33:12.830
understand about RL

00:33:12.840 --> 00:33:14.710
is like

00:33:14.720 --> 00:33:16.590
it's harder to train an agent to play

00:33:16.600 --> 00:33:19.630
2048 well, for instance, than it is to

00:33:19.640 --> 00:33:25.070
train an agent to fly a drone.

00:33:26.669 --> 00:33:26.679
So, we have a number of environments

00:33:26.679 --> 00:33:28.110
that actually

00:33:28.120 --> 00:33:31.190
uh are very, very good tests of how good

00:33:31.200 --> 00:33:33.470
your learning algorithm is.

00:33:33.480 --> 00:33:35.870
Like Neural MMO 3, for instance, this is

00:33:35.880 --> 00:33:38.110
basically a harder problem than is used

00:33:38.120 --> 00:33:40.270
in anywhere in research in the vast

00:33:40.280 --> 00:33:45.910
majority of industry.

00:33:47.550 --> 00:33:47.560
Like the driving environment here would

00:33:47.560 --> 00:33:50.390
be considered like a only medium

00:33:50.400 --> 00:33:52.390
complexity problem, and this is used by

00:33:52.400 --> 00:33:54.710
actual driving companies.

00:33:54.720 --> 00:33:58.710
Like self-driving companies.

00:34:00.550 --> 00:34:00.560
So, the things that people think are

00:34:00.560 --> 00:34:02.430
hard are often not the things that are

00:34:02.440 --> 00:34:05.150
actually hard.

00:34:05.160 --> 00:34:06.910
And we have the environments that we

00:34:06.920 --> 00:34:14.630
have for research for a reason.

00:34:16.430 --> 00:34:16.440
This is actually the core problem that a

00:34:16.440 --> 00:34:18.430
lot of um

00:34:18.440 --> 00:34:19.990
that sort of plagued a lot of the field

00:34:20.000 --> 00:34:22.149
in reinforcement learning is people

00:34:22.159 --> 00:34:23.669
really did not have a good grasp of

00:34:23.679 --> 00:34:26.470
which tasks are informative uh as to

00:34:26.480 --> 00:34:28.270
when your methods will generalize versus

00:34:28.280 --> 00:35:38.830
which ones are not.

